    (1,'Bulbasaur',45,49,49,'Grass','Poison','Overgrow','NA','Chlorophyll','6.9 kG','Green','M (87.5%)','NA','Reception to Bulbasaur has been largely positive and it often appears in "top Pokémon lists". Its English name is a portmanteau of "bulb" and "dinosaur". It shares its category with Ivysaur, Venusaur and Sunkern. They are all known as the Seed Pokémon.','https://img.pokemondb.net/sprites/black-white/normal/bulbasaur.png'),
